title: Scientists identify compounds in coffee which may inhibit prostate cancer

title_detail.value: Scientists identify compounds in coffee which may inhibit prostate cancer

summary: For the first time, scientists have identified compounds found in coffee which may inhibit the growth of prostate cancer. This is a pilot study, carried out on drug-resistant cancer cells in cell culture and in a mouse model; it has not yet been tested in humans.
